google_play_reviews.content: Surprisingly fun to play.
Underrated, great.
Very beautiful looking and sounding pinball game
What's not to like? Very fun and no downsides that I can see.

Absolutely BEAUTIFUL game with incredible graphics; simplistic but very fun, colorful, and it's easy on the eyes. Easy to understand rules and gameplay, too! It isn't too difficult, but still a nice challenge. And FINALLY, there's a pinball game WITHOUT ads! With everything being so ridden and plagued with ads these days, this is such a breath of fresh air. 5 stars from me for sure.

phenomenal, free, no ads. I play a lot of pinball and this does a good job replicating it as a mobile game. It's not pinball fx, but the graphics are crisp, rules clear, and you can control the ball just like a physical table. The ball doesn't roll up the inlanes like in the real world, but the modes are fun and table variety is great.
Literally just pinball! It delivers what is promised, without ads, and without unnecessary flair. It's pleasing to the eyes and ears, and more people need to know about this.
This game is perfect. Fun to play, easy to see unlike most pinball games. Just beautiful.

Great physics.... For a ping pong ball! It bounces all over the damn place. It's a great looking game design, but the physics need work. The flippers are too weak and the ball physics are so jangly and random as to make any real ball control virtually impossible. Not a good representation of the silver ball.

There is beauty in its simplicity.üëç‚ù§Ô∏è This is what pinball should be! There are only about 9 different tables but each one is a fun challenge of getting the highest score for a game with the option of unlimited balls without annoying adverts and earning coin to unlock levels. Everything you want and need from the futuristic hum of a space and planet themed set of tables, a real clean and ethereal quality to it. If only this was a full sized real-life pinball table.

Oh my gosh. I think I use to play this back in middle school or somewhere around that time! For me the music, the simple yet high replayability of the tables & just the contrasting dark and colorfulness of everything makes me feel so happy and it just makes me remember my younger days when I used to played this game but completely forgot about those times. Anyway it has some really nice physics & looks gorgeous on an oled screen! It doesn't really need it but could u add some more tables to it?
Sorry. It has a charm with the nice sounds and vector graphics, but the tables get boring fast. No missions or anything, its basically bird brain pinball lol.

Superb pinball game! After trying so many other pinball games, I found one without ads, undesired flashy graphics, or *story mode*; just smacking some balls around. The game play is simple and easily mastered, the tables are challenging, and there's an infinite balls option! I especially like the constellation table. I've never experienced a lag in game play. I also like the vector design. The minimalist look is easy on the eyes and battery, and I personally find it sleek. Also: NO ADS!
Super fun and simple pinball. Graphics are just the way I want it. No fancy textures, delayed inputs, fps drops or unexpected crashes. Most frequently played game on my phone. Love it.
Amazing little pinball game with great sound design and completely free!
A bonafide classic and it's free. Superb.
